---
layout: base.njk
---
<main id="top">
  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap hero-grid">
    <div>
      <span class="kicker label"><span class="dot"></span>Where next &middot; travel, sorted</span>
      <h1>Every city, one&nbsp;clear <em>next stop.</em></h1>
      <p class="lead">WHRNXT turns a place you've never been into a plan you can actually follow — sights, food, and transit for 2,300+ cities, with a trip you can share in a tap.</p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn-signal" href="{{ site.appUrl }}">Open the app &#9656;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#plan">See how it works</a>
      </div>
      <div class="trust">
        <span><b>Free</b> to use</span>
        <span><b>No login</b> needed</span>
        <span><b>Works offline</b></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="demo" id="demo">
      <div class="demo-bar">
        <span class="demo-status" id="demo-status"><span class="demo-dot"></span>Browsing New York</span>
        <span class="mono">LIVE &mdash; not a screenshot</span>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-screen">
        <iframe
          id="demo-frame"
          class="demo-frame"
          title="WHRNXT app, live demo browsing New York"
          src="{{ site.appUrl }}/?embed=1&amp;city=newyork"
          loading="lazy"
          allow="geolocation"
          referrerpolicy="origin"></iframe>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-foot">
        <button class="btn btn-signal" id="demo-locate" type="button">Use my location &#9656;</button>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="{{ site.appUrl }}">Open full app</a>
      </div>
      <p class="demo-fine" id="demo-fine">Browsing New York &mdash; no location needed. Pick any city inside, or switch to where you actually are.</p>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <div class="ticker" aria-hidden="true"><div class="ticker-in">
    <span><b>2,300+</b> cities</span><span><b>60,000+</b> places</span><span>PARIS</span><span>TOKYO</span><span>NANTUCKET</span><span><b>Works offline</b></span><span>CAPE TOWN</span><span>MOAB</span><span>KYOTO</span><span><b>No login</b></span><span>TELLURIDE</span><span>LISBON</span><span><b>Free</b></span>
    <span><b>2,300+</b> cities</span><span><b>60,000+</b> places</span><span>PARIS</span><span>TOKYO</span><span>NANTUCKET</span><span><b>Works offline</b></span><span>CAPE TOWN</span><span>MOAB</span><span>KYOTO</span><span><b>No login</b></span><span>TELLURIDE</span><span>LISBON</span><span><b>Free</b></span>
  </div></div>

  <section class="block" id="find"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="label">What it does</span>
      <h2>Get your bearings anywhere — then keep moving.</h2>
      <p>WHRNXT isn't a list of links. It's a hand-picked guide to what's worth your time in each place, measured from wherever you're standing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feat">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Find</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M12 2a7 7 0 0 0-7 7c0 5 7 13 7 13s7-8 7-13a7 7 0 0 0-7-7Zm0 9.5A2.5 2.5 0 1 1 12 6.5a2.5 2.5 0 0 1 0 5Z"/></svg>
        <h3>Sights &amp; food for 2,300+ cities</h3>
        <p>From Tokyo to a small airport town, browse the places actually worth visiting — sorted by distance, with the real transit hubs to reach them. Preview any city without turning on location.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" id="plan">
        <span class="label">Plan</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M4 5h16v2H4Zm0 6h10v2H4Zm0 6h16v2H4Z"/></svg>
        <h3>A trip that plans the walking for you</h3>
        <p>Add your stops and WHRNXT chains them into the shortest sensible day. Then it hands you a share link — friends open the exact plan, no account and no app-store detour.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" id="transit">
        <span class="label">Transit</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M12 2c-4 0-8 .5-8 4v9.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 6.5 18L5 19.5V20h2l2-2h6l2 2h2v-.5L17.5 18A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 20 15.5V6c0-3.5-4-4-8-4ZM7.5 17A1.5 1.5 0 1 1 9 15.5 1.5 1.5 0 0 1 7.5 17Zm9 0a1.5 1.5 0 1 1 1.5-1.5 1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5ZM18 11H6V6h12Z"/></svg>
        <h3>Airports &amp; stations, sorted</h3>
        <p>Every city shows its real transit. Tap "nearby cities' transit" and WHRNXT pulls in the airports and stations within reach — deduped and nearest-first, so you see one Newark, not eighteen.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Offline</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M12 3a9 9 0 1 0 9 9 9 9 0 0 0-9-9Zm6.7 7H14.4A9.9 9.9 0 0 0 12.9 5.1 7 7 0 0 1 18.7 10ZM12 5a9.9 9.9 0 0 1 1.5 5h-3A9.9 9.9 0 0 1 12 5ZM5.3 10a7 7 0 0 1 4.1-4.4A11.7 11.7 0 0 0 8 10Zm0 4H8a11.7 11.7 0 0 0 1.4 4.4A7 7 0 0 1 5.3 14ZM12 19a9.9 9.9 0 0 1-1.5-3.5h3A9.9 9.9 0 0 1 12 19Zm-1.9-5.5a13 13 0 0 1 0-3h3.8a13 13 0 0 1 0 3Zm4.5 3.9A11.7 11.7 0 0 0 16 14h2.7a7 7 0 0 1-4.1 4.4Z"/></svg>
        <h3>Works with no signal</h3>
        <p>WHRNXT runs in your browser and keeps working on the plane, underground, or abroad without data. Nothing to install, no sign-up, and it's free.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="block" id="share" style="padding-top:0"><div class="wrap"><div class="split">
    <div class="panel-lg">
      <span class="label">Community</span>
      <h2>Made a good trip? Share it.</h2>
      <p>Drop a WHRNXT share link (or any trip link). No account needed — every trip is reviewed by a human before it goes live for other travelers.</p>
      <form name="share-trip" method="POST" data-netlify="true" netlify-honeypot="bot-field" action="/thanks/">
        <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="share-trip">
        <p hidden><label>Leave blank: <input name="bot-field"></label></p>
        <label class="f" for="t-title">Trip title</label>
        <input id="t-title" name="title" placeholder="A long weekend in Lisbon" required>
        <div class="form-row">
          <div><label class="f" for="t-cities">Cities</label><input id="t-cities" name="cities" placeholder="Lisbon, Sintra"></div>
          <div><label class="f" for="t-link">Share link</label><input id="t-link" name="link" type="url" placeholder="https://app.whrnxt.net/?i=…" required></div>
        </div>
        <button class="btn btn-signal" type="submit" style="align-self:flex-start;margin-top:6px">Post trip &#9656;</button>
      </form>
      <p class="fine">Reviewed and approved before it appears &mdash; no spam, no junk links.</p>
      <a class="browse" href="{{ site.appUrl }}">Browse shared trips &#9656;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-lg">
      <span class="label">Launch list</span>
      <h2>Get the drop on the native apps.</h2>
      <p>The iPhone and Android versions are on the way. The web app is live and free today — leave your email and we'll tell you the moment the apps land.</p>
      <form name="notify" method="POST" data-netlify="true" netlify-honeypot="bot-field" action="/thanks/">
        <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="notify">
        <p hidden><label>Leave blank: <input name="bot-field"></label></p>
        <label class="f" for="n-email">Email</label>
        <input id="n-email" name="email" type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required>
        <button class="btn btn-signal" type="submit" style="align-self:flex-start;margin-top:6px">Notify me &#9656;</button>
      </form>
      <p class="fine">One email when the apps launch. No newsletter, no noise.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:26px" class="trust"><span><span class="mono" style="color:var(--go)">&#9679;</span> Web app live now</span><span><b>iOS &amp; Android</b> next</span></div>
    </div>
  </div></div></section>
</main>

{% raw %}<script>
(function(){
  var frame  = document.getElementById('demo-frame');
  var locate = document.getElementById('demo-locate');
  var status = document.getElementById('demo-status');
  var fine   = document.getElementById('demo-fine');
  if(!frame || !locate) return;

  var APP_ORIGIN = new URL(frame.src).origin;

  function send(type){
    if(frame.contentWindow) frame.contentWindow.postMessage({type:type}, APP_ORIGIN);
  }

  locate.addEventListener('click', function(){
    if(locate.dataset.mode === 'current'){ send('whrnxt:browse'); return; }
    // The iframe carries allow="geolocation", so the app's own request prompts here.
    send('whrnxt:use-location');
    locate.textContent = 'Locating…';
    locate.disabled = true;
  });

  // The app reports its mode back so the button reflects what's actually on screen.
  window.addEventListener('message', function(e){
    if(e.origin !== APP_ORIGIN) return;
    var d = e.data;
    if(!d || d.type !== 'whrnxt:mode') return;
    locate.disabled = false;
    if(d.browseMode === 'current'){
      locate.dataset.mode = 'current';
      locate.textContent = 'Back to browsing ▸';
      status.innerHTML = '<span class="demo-dot"></span>Your location';
      fine.textContent = 'Showing places near you. Switch back to browse any other city.';
    } else {
      locate.dataset.mode = 'browse';
      locate.textContent = 'Use my location ▸';
      status.innerHTML = '<span class="demo-dot"></span>Browsing' + (d.city ? '' : ' New York');
      fine.textContent = 'Browsing — no location needed. Pick any city inside, or switch to where you actually are.';
    }
  });
})();
</script>{% endraw %}
